Is there a way to change the alignment of \multirow{5}{*}, such that it centers its contents?

I want to use \multirow{5}{*} rather than \vspace*{5cm} because \vspace*{5cm} is not allowed within table and \multirow{5}{*} can be used inside tablular.

Edit: Here's an MWE setting up what I'm trying to do.
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{array}
\begin{document}
\begin{table}
    \centering
    \begin{tabular}{|c|c|}
        \hline
        1st & 2nd \\
        \hline
        3rd & 4th \\
        \hline
    \end{tabular}
    \caption{A table}
    \label{tab:example}
\end{table}
\end{document}
The reason I want to use \multirow{5}{*} is that, as I understand it, it is more flexible than \vspace*{5cm}.

You can use the "multicols" environment from the array package. As per their documentation:
\begin{center}
\textit{\textbf{Use}}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|}
    \hline
    1st & 2nd \\
    \hline
    3rd & 4th \\
    \hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\textit{\textbf{Example}}
\end{center}
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|}
    \hline
    1st & 2nd \\
    \hline
    3rd & 4th \\
    \hline
